## PROJECT LOCK

This repository is for one project only:

- `AI-Based Brain Stroke Detection and Lesion Segmentation from CT Scans`

Always keep work aligned to:

- brain CT input
- stage 1 stroke classification
- stage 2 hemorrhage lesion segmentation
- simple judge-facing interface
- reproducible and competition-compliant delivery

## COMPLIANCE LOCK

- Organizer rules override softer challenge copy.
- No external or supplementary data.
- No augmentation in official training mode.
- Dataset dimension output is mandatory before training or inference.
- Commercial AI APIs cannot be core runtime components.

## DRIFT PREVENTION

Reject or narrow work that adds:

- extra modalities
- platform sprawl
- unsupported research branches
- UI ambition beyond the judge demo
- infra work with no direct submission value

## EXECUTION BIAS

Prefer:

- simplest shippable architecture
- one canonical data path
- one canonical inference path
- explicit metrics
- documentation and validation as first-class outputs

## RUFLO + BMAD

- Route non-trivial tasks through Ruflo first.
- Use LSRA for medium or large tasks.
- Respect BMAD phase gates and checkpointing.
- Treat constitution and execution spec as active guardrails, not optional reading.
